@@TJvTransparentButton.WordWrap
Summary
  Specifies whether the text wraps when it is too long for the width of the control.
Description
  Set WordWrap to true to allow the control to display multiple line of text. When WordWrap is true,
  text that is too wide for the control wraps at the right margin and continues in additional lines.
  
  Set WordWrap to false to limit the text to a single line. When WordWrap is false, text that is too
  wide for the control appears truncated.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TControl.Caption>

